title: Accessibility
description:
All restrooms are wheelchair accessible.
Wheelchair accessible buses are available to travel around the airport. The Route A bus serves all terminals, and arrives approximately every 15 minutes between 6 a.m. and 10:30 p.m. The Route B bus serves Terminals B, C, and D, and arrives every 5 minutes (depending on traffic) between 10 a.m. and 8 p.m.

More information

title: Air Canada Maple Leaf Lounge, upper level (third floor)
Parking
description:
P1 Daily Parking

Daily Parking Rates:
1/2 hr: $4
1 hr: $8
Each additional 1/2 hr or part thereof*: $4
24-hr maximum: $39
* charges are incurred in half-hour increments before reaching the daily maximum

Take the free Route A (all terminals) or Route B (all terminals except Marine Air Terminal / Delta Shuttle) courtesy buses to transfer between parking lots and terminals. Route A buses run every 10 to 15 minutes from 4:00 a.m. to 11:30 p.m. and Route B buses run every 10 to 15 minutes from 6:00 a.m. to 2:00 a.m.

More information

description:

title: Rental Cars
description:
Rental cars, trucks and other vehicles are also available at LaGuardia through a number of car rental companies. Please check with them directly for availability, reservations and costs. In addition, these rental agencies provide frequent free shuttle bus service between LaGuardia's terminals and their pickup/drop-off locations.

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description:
Taxis
Taxi service is available in front of all terminals. Disregard offers of transportation from solicitors in the terminal. Be sure your transportation is safe and legitimate at ground transportation information counters, bus stops and taxi dispatchers.

Car and Van Service
Shared-ride van and private car services are available at every terminal.

More information

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description:
Airport Shuttle
The NYC Airporter provides service to Port Authority Bus Terminal, Grand Central Station and Penn Station. NYCAirporter also offers free shuttle van service to Times Square & mid-town hotels between 23rd and 63rd Streets for NYC Airporter shuttle bus customers.

Please look for the NYC Airporter ticket sales counter or Agents (wearing green coats in the winter/ white shirts in the summer) outside of baggage claim, and at the Ground Transportation Welcome Centers at each Airport Terminal.
More information

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description:
Local Bus Service
New York City buses provide service between LaGuardia and Manhattan and Queens with connections to New York City subways.
Routes M60, Q47 and Q48 serve terminal A.
